  "text": "The meta-analysis conducted by Steenbergen and Cooper in 2013 analyzed the effectiveness of ITSs on k-12 students' math learning [CITATION_1] . This empirical research examined 26 reports comparing the effectiveness of ITSs with that of regular classroom instruction. Their finding was that ITSs did not have a significant effect on student learning outcomes when used for a short period. However, the effectiveness appeared to be greater when ITS was used for one full school year or longer. In addition, the effects appeared to be greater on general students than on low achievers.",
